[src:insecure-deserialization/deserialization-cheat-sheet] A great reduction of risk is achieved by avoiding native (de)serialization formats.
[src:insecure-deserialization/deserialization-cheat-sheet] By switching to a pure data format like JSON or XML, you lessen the chance of custom deserialization logic being repurposed towards malicious ends.
[src:insecure-deserialization/deserialization-cheat-sheet] Many applications rely on a data-transfer object pattern that involves creating a separate domain of objects for the explicit purpose data transfer.
