[src:insecure-deserialization/object-computer-science] If the language also provides polymorphism and inheritance it is classified as object-oriented.
[src:insecure-deserialization/object-computer-science] A language that supports creating an object from a class is classified as class-based.
[src:insecure-deserialization/object-computer-science] A language that supports object creation via a template object is classified as prototype-based.
[src:insecure-deserialization/object-computer-science] In purely object-oriented programming languages, such as Java and C#, all classes might be part of an inheritance tree such that the root class is `Object`, meaning all objects instances of `Object` or implicitly extend `Object`.
